<NAME type="xs:string"></NAME><APP_NAME type="xs:string">Undiscoverable scanner apps</APP_NAME><VENDOR type="xs:string">Multiple</VENDOR><EXE_ID type="xs:string" baseType="xs:base64Binary">{87136f35-ffd8-46ee-9b4a-d8ba442c2343}</EXE_ID><APP_ID type="xs:base64Binary" /><DEST_OS_GTE type="xs:string">GE24H2</DEST_OS_GTE><DEST_OS_LT type="xs:string">XY30H1</DEST_OS_LT><MATCH_PLUGIN><NAME type="xs:string">PowerShellMatchingPlugin</NAME><COMMAND_LINE type="xs:string">
                    $Res = 0
                    $LastVidPid = ''
                    $UsbDevices = Get-PnpDevice | Sort-Object InstanceId | Where-Object { $_.InstanceId -like '*usb\vid_*' }
                    Write-Host $UsbDevices.Count, 'USB devices'
                    foreach ($d in $UsbDevices) {
                        $InstParts = $d.InstanceId -split '&'
                        if ($InstParts.Count -lt 2) { continue }
                        $VidPid = $InstParts[0] + '&' + $InstParts[1]
                        if ($VidPid -ne $LastVidPid) {
                            # Consider all instances of this VID/PID
                            $ThisDevice = $UsbDevices | Where-Object { $_.InstanceId -and $_.InstanceId.Contains($VidPid) }
                            $HasPrint = $ThisDevice | Where-Object { $_.CompatibleID -and $_.CompatibleID.Contains('USB\Class_07&SubClass_01&Prot_02') }
                            if ($HasPrint) {
                                # No need to block an update for device with USB print
                                # Do nothing
                            }
                            else {
                                $HasScan = $ThisDevice | Where-Object { $_.CompatibleID -and $_.CompatibleID.Contains('USB\MS_COMP_SCAN') }
                                if ($HasScan) {
                                    Write-Host 'Block update for:', $thisDevice[0].InstanceID
                                    $Res = 1
                                    break
                                }

                                $HasWinUSB = $ThisDevice | Where-Object { $_.CompatibleID -and $_.CompatibleID.Contains('USB\MS_COMP_WINUSB') }
                                if ($HasWinUSB) {
                                    Write-Host 'Block update for:', $thisDevice[0].InstanceID
                                    $Res = 1
                                    break
                                }
                            }
                            $LastVidPid = $VidPid
                        }
                    }
                    Write-Host 'Final result:', $Res
                </COMMAND_LINE></MATCH_PLUGIN><DATA><NAME type="xs:string">AppraiserData</NAME><DATA_VALUETYPE type="xs:int">1</DATA_VALUETYPE><DATA_STRING type="xs:string">GatedBlock</DATA_STRING></DATA><DATA><NAME type="xs:string">AppraiserData_GatedBlockId</NAME><DATA_VALUETYPE type="xs:int">1</DATA_VALUETYPE><DATA_STRING type="xs:string">54762729</DATA_STRING></DATA>

<NAME type="xs:string"></NAME><APP_NAME type="xs:string">Low disk space devices (Wu Offer Block)</APP_NAME><VENDOR type="xs:string">Microsoft</VENDOR><EXE_ID type="xs:string" baseType="xs:base64Binary">{c8edd7b8-7316-49b7-908d-56952bd3bb0d}</EXE_ID><APP_ID type="xs:base64Binary" /><DEST_OS_GTE type="xs:string">GE24H2</DEST_OS_GTE><DEST_OS_LT type="xs:string">XY30H1</DEST_OS_LT><MATCH_PLUGIN><NAME type="xs:string">PowerShellMatchingPlugin</NAME><COMMAND_LINE type="xs:string">
                    $Res = 0
                    [UInt64]$MinDiskSpaceThreshold = 25 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024

                    try {
                        $SystemDrive = (Get-CimInstance Win32_OperatingSystem).SystemDrive
                        $SystemDriveLetter = $SystemDrive[0]
                        $SystemDriveSpace = (Get-Volume -DriveLetter $SystemDriveLetter).SizeRemaining
                        Write-Host 'Current system drive space:', $SystemDriveSpace.ToString('N0')
                        if ($SystemDriveSpace -lt $MinDiskSpaceThreshold) {
                            Write-Host 'System drive space is less than the threshold:', $MinDiskSpaceThreshold.ToString('N0'), 'Applying safeguard.'
                            $Res = 1
                        }
                    } catch {
                        # Do nothing
                    }

                    Write-Host 'Final result:', $Res
                </COMMAND_LINE></MATCH_PLUGIN><DATA><NAME type="xs:string">AppraiserData</NAME><DATA_VALUETYPE type="xs:int">1</DATA_VALUETYPE><DATA_STRING type="xs:string">GatedBlock</DATA_STRING></DATA><DATA><NAME type="xs:string">AppraiserData_GatedBlockId</NAME><DATA_VALUETYPE type="xs:int">1</DATA_VALUETYPE><DATA_STRING type="xs:string">56031903</DATA_STRING></DATA>

<NAME type="xs:string"></NAME><APP_NAME type="xs:string">Corrupted desktop in HDR/ACM mode</APP_NAME><VENDOR type="xs:string">Intel</VENDOR><EXE_ID type="xs:string" baseType="xs:base64Binary">{77b4ac2c-3c6f-49b8-a80a-432dc96cb1d1}</EXE_ID><APP_ID type="xs:base64Binary" /><DEST_OS_GTE type="xs:string">GE24H2</DEST_OS_GTE><DEST_OS_LT type="xs:string">XY30H1</DEST_OS_LT><PICK_ONE><MATCHING_REG><NAME type="xs:string">SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\GraphicsDrivers\FeatureSetUsage</NAME><REG_VALUE_NAME type="xs:string">DisplayHDR</REG_VALUE_NAME><REG_VALUE_TYPE type="xs:int">4</REG_VALUE_TYPE><REG_VALUE_DATA_DWORD type="xs:int">1</REG_VALUE_DATA_DWORD></MATCHING_REG><MATCHING_REG><NAME type="xs:string">SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\GraphicsDrivers\FeatureSetUsage</NAME><REG_VALUE_NAME type="xs:string">DisplayWCG</REG_VALUE_NAME><REG_VALUE_TYPE type="xs:int">4</REG_VALUE_TYPE><REG_VALUE_DATA_DWORD type="xs:int">1</REG_VALUE_DATA_DWORD></MATCHING_REG></PICK_ONE><MATCH_PLUGIN><NAME type="xs:string">PowerShellMatchingPlugin</NAME><COMMAND_LINE type="xs:string">
                    function Test-DeviceRunningKnownBadDriver {
                        param ( $intelDisplayAdapters )

                        Write-Host 'Test-DeviceRunningKnownBadDriver called'

                        # List of Tiger Lake hardware ids.
                        $tigerLakeHardwareIds = [System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]::new([string[]]@('pci\ven_8086&dev_9a49','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a68','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a60','pci\ven_8086&dev_9ac9','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a59','pci\ven_8086&dev_9af8','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a78','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a70','pci\ven_8086&dev_9ac0','pci\ven_8086&dev_9ad9','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a40'));

                        $driverVersionMatch = $false;
                        $chipsetSeriesMatch = $false;

                        # Now get the first two parts of the Instance Id and match it against the known list of TGL HWIDs.
                        $intelDisplayAdapters | ForEach-Object {
                            if($_.InstanceId -ne $null) {
                                $parts = $_.InstanceId.ToLower() -split '&';
                                if($parts.Length -ge 2) {
                                    $combined = $parts[0] + '&' + $parts[1];
                                    $chipsetSeriesMatch = $chipsetSeriesMatch -or $tigerLakeHardwareIds.Contains($combined);
                                }
                            }
                        }

                        # Proceed to driver version check if Chipset series matches.
                        if($chipsetSeriesMatch -eq $true) { 
                            # For each Intel GPU, get the driver version installed.
                            $driverVersionsInstalled = $intelDisplayAdapters | ForEach-Object {
                                if ($_.InstanceId -ne $null) {
                                    Get-PnpDeviceProperty -InstanceId $_.InstanceId -KeyName DEVPKEY_Device_DriverVersion | Select-Object Data
                                }
                            };

                            # If we couldn't get the driver version, return false.
                            if($driverVersionsInstalled -eq $null -or $driverVersionsInstalled.Data -eq $null) { return 0; }

                            $driverVersionsInstalled | ForEach-Object {
                                if($_.Data -eq '32.0.101.5972' -or $_.Data -eq '32.0.101.6078') {
                                    $driverVersionMatch = $true;
                                } 
                            }

                            if($driverVersionMatch -eq $true) { return 1; } else { return 0; }
                        }

                        # Default to no match.
                        return 0;
                    }

                    function Test-DeviceIsAtRiskOfReceivingKnownBadDriver {
                        param ( $intelDisplayAdapters )

                        Write-Host 'Test-DeviceIsAtRiskOfReceivingKnownBadDriver called'

                        # Known list of impacted Intel hardware ids.
                        $targetHardwareIds = [System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]::new([string[]]@('pci\ven_8086&dev_9a60','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a68','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a70','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a49&subsys_22d517aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a49&subsys_22d417aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a78&subsys_22d417aa','pci\ven_8086dev_9a49&subsys_00601414','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a40&subsys_22c717aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a78&subsys_22d517aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a40&subsys_22d417aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a49&subsys_22c717aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a78','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a78&subsys_22c717aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a40&subsys_22d517aa','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a49','pci\ven_8086&dev_9a40')); 

                        # Define the flags.
                        $hardwareIDMatch = $false;

                        # For each Intel GPU, get the associated matching device Id.
                        $matchingDeviceIds = $intelDisplayAdapters | ForEach-Object {Get-PnpDeviceProperty -InstanceId $_.InstanceId -KeyName DEVPKEY_Device_MatchingDeviceId | Select-Object Data}; 

                        # Terminate if we can not obtain matching device id PnP property.
                        if($matchingDeviceIds -eq $null -or $matchingDeviceIds.Data -eq $null) { return 0; }

                        # For each matching device Id, check to see if it matches with any item in our known bad HWID list.
                        $matchingDeviceIds.Data | ForEach-Object { $hardwareIDMatch = $hardwareIDMatch -or $targetHardwareIds.Contains($_.ToLower()) } | Out-Null; 

                        if ($hardwareIDMatch) { return 1; }

                        # Default to no match.
                        return 0;
                    }

                    $Match = 0

                    # Get all Intel Display Adapters available on the device
                    $intelDisplayAdapters = Get-PnpDevice | Where-Object { $_.Class -eq 'Display' -and $_.InstanceId -match 'PCI\\VEN_8086&*' };

                    if ($intelDisplayAdapters) {
                        $Match = Test-DeviceRunningKnownBadDriver -intelDisplayAdapters $intelDisplayAdapters
                        if ($Match -eq 0) {
                            $Match = Test-DeviceIsAtRiskOfReceivingKnownBadDriver -intelDisplayAdapters $intelDisplayAdapters
                        }
                    }

                    Write-Host 'Final result:', $Match
                </COMMAND_LINE></MATCH_PLUGIN><DATA><NAME type="xs:string">AppraiserData</NAME><DATA_VALUETYPE type="xs:int">1</DATA_VALUETYPE><DATA_STRING type="xs:string">GatedBlock</DATA_STRING></DATA><DATA><NAME type="xs:string">AppraiserData_GatedBlockId</NAME><DATA_VALUETYPE type="xs:int">1</DATA_VALUETYPE><DATA_STRING type="xs:string">54853601</DATA_STRING></DATA>
